'''抗議'''（{{lang-en|Protest}}）指的是對某些人、某國、某單位的言論、行為或措施表示強烈反對的行為，在社會學與政治學上常指群體性的反對行為<ref>{{cite web |title=抗议 |url=https://www.zdic.net/hans/%E6%8A%97%E8%AE%AE |website=汉典 |accessdate=2020-09-30 |archive-date=2021-02-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210218110954/https://www.zdic.net/hans/%E6%8A%97%E8%AE%AE |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/protest|title=Definition of PROTEST|website=www.merriam-webster.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04|archive-date=2021-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210218110957/https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/protest|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macmillandictionary.com/dictionary/british/protest_1|title=PROTEST (noun) definition and synonyms {{!}} Macmillan Dictionary|website=www.macmillandictionary.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04|archive-date=2021-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210218111020/https://www.macmillandictionary.com/dictionary/british/protest_1|dead-url=no}}</ref>。抗議的方式多種多樣，從個人在街頭演講到某個群體在街頭進行[[示威|示威]]的行为等。抗議者可能通過公開、有力的方式組織抗議，使其意見被聽取，來試圖影響大眾[[舆论|舆论]]或者[[政府|政府]]政策，也可能採取[[直接行动|直接行动]]，來試圖直接制定它們想要的改變<ref>St. John Barned-Smith, "How We Rage: This Is Not Your Parents' Protest, " ''Current'' (Winter 2007): 17-25.</ref>。如果抗議是為實現特定目標而進行的系統性的、和平的[[非暴力|非暴力]]運動的一部分，並且涉及使用壓力和說服力，則抗議会被认为不仅仅是单纯的抗议而是[[公民抵抗|公民抵抗]]或[[非暴力抵抗|非暴力抵抗]]<ref name=CivilResistance>{{cite book|first=Adam|last=Roberts|author-link=Adam Roberts (scholar)|editor-first=Timothy Garton|editor-last=Ash|editor-link=Timothy Garton Ash|title=Civil Resistance and Power Politics: The Experience of Non-violent Action from Gandhi to the Present|url=https://archive.org/details/civilresistancep00robe|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2009|isbn=978-0-19-955201-6|pages=[https://archive.org/details/civilresistancep00robe/page/n24 2]–3}}</ref>。

由於多樣化的自我表現及抗議在理論、實踐或外觀上可能被政府的政策（比如需要申请{{le|抗议许可|Protest permit}}）<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Controlling+public+protest%3a+First+Amendment+implications.-a016473804|title=Controlling Public Protest: First Amendment Implications|accessdate=16 December 2009|author=Daniel L. Schofield, S.J.D.|date=November 1994|publisher=in the [[联邦调查局|FBI]]'s [[FBI_Law_Enforcement_Bulletin|Law Enforcement Bulletin]]|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224155709/https://www.thefreelibrary.com/Controlling+public+protest%3a+First+Amendment+implications.-a016473804|dead-url=no}}</ref>，經濟環境，宗教規範，社會結構或媒體壟斷所限制。出动[[防暴警察|防暴警察]]即為政府的一種常見應對方法。

抗議自身有时可能是緣由{{Link-en|反抗議|Counter-protest}}。這種情況下，反抗議者會針對原抗議的反對行為進行抗議。

